Executive Profile
Michael D. Capellas  Non-Executive Chairman, Flex Ltd.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 7 Board Members in 7 different organizations across 20 different industries.See Board Relationships62$274,944
Background

		Mr. Michael D. Capellas founded Capellas Partners and serves as its Principal and Chief Executive Officer. Mr. Capellas serves as Principal, Founder and Chief Executive Officer of. Mr. Capellas served as the Head of Cloud Computing to Business Clients at EMC Corporation. He served as a Senior Advisor at Kohlberg Kravis Roberts & Co. L.P. He served as the Head of Joint Ventures at Cisco Systems, Inc. since May 2010. His career spans more than 30 years in the technology ... industry. He has been Chairman of the Board of JDA Software Group, Inc. since January 30, 2017. He served as the Chief Executive Officer of VCE Company, LLC (also known as Virtual Computing Environment) from May 2010 to July 2012 and served as its Chairman. He served as the Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of First Data Corporation from September 24, 2010 to March 31, 2013 and served as its Adviser. He served as Senior Advisor at KKR & Co. L.P. (KKR & Co Guernsey LP) since March 2010. He served as the Chief Executive Officer and Chairman of Compaq Computer Corp. since June 1999 and July 1990 respectively. He joined Compaq in 1998 as Chief Information Officer. Mr. Capellas served as the President of Dynegy Inc. and Hewlett-Packard Company. He served as the Chief Executive Officer and President of Verizon Business Global LLC since December 17, 2002 and served as its Chairman from December 17, 2002 to March 16, 2004. He served as Chief Executive Officer and President of Worldcom Group. He served as the Chief Executive Officer and President of Intermedia Investment Inc., Business Internet Inc. and Intermedia Communications Inc. He served as an Acting Chief Executive Officer and Acting President at Serena Software, Inc. from December 2006 to February 26, 2007. He began his career with Schlumberger Limited. He held senior management positions at Oracle Corporation and SAP America, Inc. He served as Senior Executive officer of Oracle Corporation. He served as Chief Executive Officer and Chairman of MCI Group (MCI, Inc.) since December 2002 and served as its President since March 16, 2004 (for 3 years). He served as Senior Advisor to Silver Lake. He has tremendous operational, financial and technology industry experience spanning hardware, software, network and communications companies. He has been Chairman of the Board at Flex Ltd. (alternatively Flextronics International Ltd.) since June 29, 2017. Mr. Capellas served as the Chairman at VCE Company, LLC from January 2011 to November 2012. He served as Chairman of the Board at Worldcom Group since December 2002 and also served as its Director. He has been Director of JDA Software Group, Inc. since October, 2016. He has been a Director of MuleSoft, Inc. since July 2015 and serves as its Lead Independent Director. He served as Lead Director of Tenable Network Security, Inc. since June 24, 2015. He has been an Non Executive Director Director of Flextronics International Ltd. since March 20, 2014 and Cisco Systems, Inc. since January 31, 2006. He serves as a Member of Americas Advisory Board at Deutsche Bank AG. He has been Member of Advisory Board at Kony, Inc., since July 2015. He has been a Member of Client Advisory at Deutsche Bank Trust Company Americas since January 25, 2007. He served as a Member of Board of Governors at Boys & Girls Clubs of America, Inc. He served as Director of Dynegy Inc. and MCI Group. He served as a Director of Verizon Business Global LLC since December 17, 2002. He served as a Director of First Data Corporation until March 31, 2010. He served as Sole Director of Business Internet Inc., Intermedia Communications Inc and Intermedia Investment Inc. He served as a Director of Compaq Computer Corp. since July 1999. Mr. Capellas holds a Bachelor's Degree in Business Administration from Kent State University.Read Full Background




